# Measure of Central Tendency

Central Tendency tells us the center value of data.

---

## Mean (Average)

Formula

```text
Mean = Sum of observations / Number of observations
```

### Python Code

```python
import numpy as np

data = [10,20,30,40,50]

mean = np.mean(data)

print(mean)
```

Output

```text
30
```

---

## Median

Middle value after sorting.

### Python Code

```python
import numpy as np

data = [10,20,30,40,50]

median = np.median(data)

print(median)
```

Output

```text
30
```

---

## Mode

Most frequently occurring value.

### Python Code

```python
from scipy import stats

data = [1,2,2,2,3,4]

mode = stats.mode(data)

print(mode)
```

Output

```text
