# Measure of Dispersion

Measures spread of data.

---

## Range

```text
Range = Maximum - Minimum
```

### Code

```python
data=[10,20,30,40,50]

range_value=max(data)-min(data)

print(range_value)
```

Output

```text
40
```

---

## Variance

Measures variability.

### Code

```python
import numpy as np

data=[10,20,30,40,50]

print(np.var(data))
```

Output

```text
200
```

---

## Standard Deviation

Square root of variance.

### Code

```python
import numpy as np

data=[10,20,30,40,50]

print(np.std(data))
```

Output

```text
14.14
```

---

## Quartile Deviation

```python
import numpy as np

data=[10,20,30,40,50]

q1=np.percentile(data,25)

q3=np.percentile(data,75)

qd=(q3-q1)/2

print(qd)
```

---

## Coefficient of Variation

```python
import numpy as np

data=[10,20,30,40,50]

cv=(np.std(data)/np.mean(data))*100

print(cv)
```

