# Outlier Analysis

### IQR Method

```python
import numpy as np

data=[1,2,3,4,5,100]

q1=np.percentile(data,25)

q3=np.percentile(data,75)

iqr=q3-q1

lower=q1-1.5*iqr

upper=q3+1.5*iqr

outliers=[
x for x in data
if x<lower or x>upper
]

print(outliers)
```

Output

```text
[100]
```

