# Hypothesis Testing

---

## Step 1

Define Hypothesis

### Null Hypothesis (H₀)

```text
No Difference
```

### Alternative Hypothesis (H₁)

```text
There is Difference
```

---

## Step 2

Select Significance Level

Usually

```text
α = 0.05
```

---

## Step 3

Select Test

* t-test
* z-test
* chi-square
* ANOVA

---

## Step 4

Calculate Test Statistic

---

## Step 5

Calculate p-value

---

## Step 6

Decision

```text
p < 0.05
Reject H0
```

```text
p > 0.05
Accept H0
```

---

# Type I Error

Reject true H0

```text
False Positive
```

---

# Type II Error

Accept false H0

```text
False Negative
```

---

# t-Test

Compare means of two groups.

```python
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

group1=[80,85,90,88]

group2=[70,75,78,72]

t,p=ttest_ind(
group1,
group2
)

print(t)
print(p)
```

---

# z-Test

```python
from statsmodels.stats.weightstats import ztest

data=[80,85,90,88,95]

print(
ztest(data,
value=80)
)
```

---

# Chi-Square Test

Categorical Data

```python
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency

table=[
[10,20],
[20,40]
]

chi,p,dof,exp=chi2_contingency(table)

print(p)
```

---

# ANOVA (F-Test)

Compare 3 or more groups.

```python
from scipy.stats import f_oneway

group1=[10,20,30]

group2=[40,50,60]

group3=[70,80,90]

f,p=f_oneway(
group1,
group2,
group3
)

print(f)
print(p)
```

